	   <tr><td colspan=2>I had a similar prob with my pally Dwarf. until i realized i have to put the time in getting my casting skills up. lately i have been thinking about going to unrest, so i thot i had better get my evocation up so i don't fizzle too much , it was at 30 ish & i failed 8 for 10. I now keep Ward<br>loaded in a slot & use it whenever i can . I was out killing spiderling for silk the last 2 days to get my tailoring skill up to make leather padding. I blasted every undead thing i saw , i am at 120 evocation now & hrdly ever fail at ward.<br>My divination was at 25 the other day & while i waited for the boat On the docks of east Freeport i cast sense undead repeatededly until the boat came , 20min. later . I gained 30 skill points & almost drained my mana, ( started at full charge).<br>I can now cast invis to undead with 2 of 10 success. So now i will keep mashing the sense undead spell til i am past 100 skill . <br>Takes time & boring to get some skills up , but if you plan it, you will get them all up. I was in the highhold zone , in Kithcor forest waiting for daylight to cross zone, so i sensed undead, was placed in the direction , so i blasted some undead pet i could not see & my evocation also went up. what a cool way to wait for daylight. hehe, if i had enough mana i prob could have killed the pet i could not see , but i could see his life bar deminish, i could have got exp. i assume if i actually killed it. I tdid not attack me, wierd. Now that i can cast the higher lvl ward<br>nwxt time i am there i will kill those undead that can not attack me , to see if i get exp.<br>Keep working those skills!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
