	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sorry to disagree, but I have a Paladin in the 20s now, and he is a Half Elf, with a WIS of 65. Sure, if you want to rely on casting there are better races, like High Elves or Humans. But you will not cast that much in the beginning, my spells fizzle 1 out of 10 if at all.<br>The most important part about a Paladin in the teens is the Healing line of spells. They do not fizzle at all with my char, guess I saw it 2 or 3 times in my whole career. Casting shall only be a support skill, not a 50/50 -thing. If you want to cast more and efficiently use a cleric.<br><br>And most importantly, the WIS-skill is not responsible for success of casting, only for mana ressources. Success is determined by DEX and level in the spell skill. I have a DEX of 114, so this may be the reason my casting is better than yours.<br><br>The only time I would agree with you is the usage of the undead series of spells. Ward undead fizzles very often, because I had no spell previously to train the evocation skill. After doing some killed skeletons with the spell I had it up to max.<br><br>Just my 2 cents.<br><br>May Mithaniel Marr guide you.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Arakonn Dragonblade<br>Grandmaster<br>Nova Militia Templaris<br>www.nova-militia.com<br></td></tr>
